Uses of Class
com.opencredo.concursus.domain.common.AggregateId

  • Packages that use AggregateId 
    Package Description
    com.opencredo.concursus.cassandra.events
    This package provides Cassandra implementations of the EventPersister, EventRetriever, AggregateCatalogue and EventStore interfaces, for persisting and retrieving event histories and keeping track of "live" aggregates.
    com.opencredo.concursus.domain.commands
    Defines a Command and the things that can be done with it.
    com.opencredo.concursus.domain.common
    Domain classes that are common to Commands and Events.
    com.opencredo.concursus.domain.events
    Defines the core Event type, and (in sub-packages) all of the things that can be done with events by event-handling middleware.
    com.opencredo.concursus.domain.events.indexing
    Provides the experimental EventIndex and EventIndexer interfaces, for classes which index aggregate ids by the most recent values assigned to parameters of events recorded against each aggregate.
    com.opencredo.concursus.domain.events.selection
    Provides the EventSelection utility class for selecting Events matching various criteria.
    com.opencredo.concursus.domain.events.sourcing
    Provides the EventSource and CachedEventSource interfaces, which represent sources of Events.
    com.opencredo.concursus.domain.events.storage
    Defines the EventStore interface, which represents an event store which can persist and retrieve events, and provides an InMemoryEventStore implementation.
    com.opencredo.concursus.mapping.events.pojos  
    com.opencredo.concursus.redis
